title: "What's Your Home Worth?"
description: "Get a real, current read on your St. Petersburg home's value — a broker's market opinion (CMA), not an automated estimate. No obligation, no pressure."
crumbs: []
---
{#- /valuation/ — plan §2 #3 / §8.1. The GUIDED AI-CMA intake (launch-checklist
    #1, built 2026-07-10): a question-by-question conversational intake
    (assets/valuation-guided.js) → a broker-prepared range report within a day —
    a human-backed CMA request, never an on-site AVM / point estimate
    (compliance GREEN-AMBER, Art. 16.03). DESIGN CALLS (surfaced to the
    operator, not silently made):
    · The flow is DETERMINISTIC (scripted questions in the chat idiom), not an
      LLM conversation — the intake collects PII, which must reach only the
      RLS-locked sink, never a model/log (the page's published privacy posture
      is Lane-records-no-PII); a script also structurally cannot fabricate a
      number. The AI halves live elsewhere: Lane below for questions (PII-free),
      comp analysis broker-side at feed time (checklist #6).
    · The classic valuation-REQUEST form (the earlier interim) REMAINS as the
      server-rendered no-JS default and a visible "prefer a simple form" swap.
    · One network path for both surfaces: window.elValuationSend in site.js —
      PREVIEW_MODE-guarded, endpoint preserved-but-inert on preview, payload
      schema-identical to the classic form (guided answers compose into
      `notes`; source: "valuation-guided") so the n8n sink needs no change.
      valuation-guided.js carries NO network primitive (check.mjs enforces). -#}

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Thinking about your own place?</p>
    <h1>What&rsquo;s your home worth right now?</h1>
    <p class="lede lede--wide">The market has moved. Get a real, current read on your home&rsquo;s value and your equity picture &mdash; a broker&rsquo;s market opinion (a CMA), no obligation, no pressure. Not an appraisal, not an automated valuation funnel.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" style="padding-top:10px">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="grid grid--2">
      <div>
        {#- The guided intake panel — hidden until valuation-guided.js boots
            (progressive enhancement: no JS → the classic form below is the
            surface, exactly as before). All content inside .chat-log and
            [data-val-answer] is script-built; the intro bubble is server-
            rendered so the panel opens mid-conversation, like /ask. -#}
        <div class="val-guided" data-val-guided hidden>
          <div class="chat-panel chat-panel--guided">
            <div class="chat-panel__id">
              <h2 class="chat-panel__name">Guided valuation</h2><span class="chat-panel__sub">&mdash; a couple of minutes, question by question</span>
            </div>
            <div class="chat-body">
              {% if site.preview %}<p class="form-disabled-note" role="note">Preview &mdash; sending is disabled</p>{% endif %}
              <div class="chat-log" role="log" aria-live="polite" aria-label="Guided valuation intake">
                <div class="chat-msg chat-msg--bot">
                  <div class="chat-bubble">Let&rsquo;s get you a real read on your home. A few quick questions about the home itself &mdash; then where to send the finished read. Nothing goes anywhere until you confirm at the end. I prepare every valuation personally: real comparable sales, a clear range, and the why &mdash; usually within a day.</div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="val-answer" data-val-answer></div>
              {#- Post-send links — server-rendered (HtmlBasePlugin rewrites the
                  hrefs for the preview path prefix); unhidden by the script
                  after a successful send. -#}
              <p class="val-done-links" data-val-done hidden>
                <a href="/guides/">Browse the guides meanwhile &rarr;</a>
                <a href="#val-ask">Or ask Lane a question below &darr;</a>
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div data-val-classic>
        <h2 style="font-size:1.3rem">Request an honest read</h2>
        <p class="form-disabled-note" role="note">Preview &mdash; form disabled</p>
        <div class="form-status" data-form-status role="status" aria-live="polite"></div>
        <form id="valuation-form" novalidate>
          <fieldset class="form-preview-disabled" disabled>
            <div class="hp" aria-hidden="true">
              <label>Leave this field empty<input type="text" name="company" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off"></label>
            </div>

            <div class="field">
              <label for="v-address">Property address <span class="hint">&mdash; the home you&rsquo;d like valued</span></label>
              <input type="text" id="v-address" name="address" autocomplete="street-address" required>
            </div>

            <div class="field">
              <label for="v-name">Your name</label>
              <input type="text" id="v-name" name="name" autocomplete="name" required>
            </div>

            <div class="grid grid--2">
              <div class="field">
                <label for="v-email">Email</label>
                <input type="email" id="v-email" name="email" autocomplete="email" required>
              </div>
              <div class="field">
                <label for="v-phone">Cell <span class="hint">(optional)</span></label>
                <input type="tel" id="v-phone" name="phone" autocomplete="tel">
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="field">
              <label for="v-timeline">Where are you in the process? <span class="hint">(optional)</span></label>
              <select id="v-timeline" name="timeline">
                <option value="">Prefer not to say</option>
                <option value="curious">Just curious what it&rsquo;s worth</option>
                <option value="weighing">Weighing a sale (next 3&ndash;6 months)</option>
                <option value="soon">Ready to sell soon</option>
                <option value="equity">Refinance / equity check</option>
              </select>
            </div>

            <div class="field">
              <label for="v-notes">Anything I should know? <span class="hint">&mdash; recent updates, beds/baths, what prompted this</span></label>
              <textarea id="v-notes" name="notes" placeholder="Optional, but it sharpens the read."></textarea>
            </div>

            <p class="consent-note">By sending this, you&rsquo;re asking Serge Osaulenko (Everlane Realty) to prepare and follow up with a market opinion on your home. Your details are used only for that &mdash; never sold or shared. You can ask to be removed anytime.</p>
            <p class="consent-note"><strong>Your privacy:</strong> the information you share here is stored securely, used only to respond to your request, never sold, rented, or shared with third parties, and deleted whenever you ask.</p>

            <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary btn--block" data-submit>Request my home value</button>
          </fieldset>
        </form>
        </div>

        <p class="val-swap" data-val-swap hidden>
          <button type="button" class="val-swap__btn" data-val-swap-btn>Prefer a simple form? Use the classic version</button>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="val-context">
        <div class="stub-block">
          <strong>What you&rsquo;ll get</strong>
          <ul style="margin:8px 0 0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.6">
            <li>A <strong>human-backed CMA</strong> &mdash; my read on your home&rsquo;s current value from real comparable sales, not an automated point estimate.</li>
            <li>Usually back to you <strong>within a day</strong>, personally.</li>
            <li>No obligation, no pressure &mdash; curious counts.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="stub-block" style="margin-top:18px">
          <strong>How it works</strong>
          <ol style="margin:8px 0 0;padding-left:20px;line-height:1.6">
            <li>Tell me about the home &mdash; the address and anything that matters (recent updates, beds/baths).</li>
            <li>I pull the real comparable sales and read them the way an automated estimate can&rsquo;t.</li>
            <li>You get a broker&rsquo;s market opinion &mdash; a clear range, and the why &mdash; usually within a day.</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
        <div class="stub-block" style="margin-top:18px">
          <strong>Why a person, not an algorithm</strong>
          <p style="margin:8px 0 0">An instant online estimate never walked your street or saw your kitchen. A broker&rsquo;s CMA weighs the comparable sales, the condition, and what&rsquo;s actually moving in your neighborhood right now &mdash; the difference between a number and a real read.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- The assistant, embedded underneath (operator 2026-07-10): the dark Lane
    entry module — for anyone who'd rather ask how a broker valuation works than
    fill the form. Plain GET form → deep-links into /ask (no network path here). -#}
<section class="section" style="padding-top:0" id="val-ask">
  <div class="wrap">
    <form class="home-ask" action="/ask/" method="get" role="search" aria-label="Ask Lane, Everlane's assistant">
      <div class="home-ask__id">
        <span class="home-ask__name">Lane</span><span class="home-ask__sub">&mdash; Everlane&rsquo;s assistant</span>
      </div>
      <p class="home-ask__lead">Questions before you start &mdash; or while you wait for your read? Ask Lane how a broker valuation actually works &mdash; grounded answers from Everlane&rsquo;s knowledge base, with a real broker behind them. Lane never asks for your details; the guided intake above is how the valuation itself gets requested.</p>
      <div class="home-ask__row">
        <label for="val-ask-input" class="sr-only">Ask Lane a question</label>
        <input id="val-ask-input" name="q" type="text" maxlength="500" autocomplete="off" placeholder="Ask about pricing, comps, flood zones, or the selling process…">
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary">Ask</button>
      </div>
      <div class="home-ask__chips">
        <span class="home-ask__try">Try</span>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=How%20is%20a%20broker%20CMA%20different%20from%20an%20online%20estimate%3F">CMA vs. online estimate</a>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=Does%20the%20flood%20zone%20affect%20a%20home%E2%80%99s%20value%3F">Flood zone &amp; value</a>
        <a class="chip" href="/ask/?q=How%20does%20selling%20a%20home%20in%20St.%20Pete%20work%3F">How selling works</a>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</section>
<script src="/assets/valuation-guided.js" defer></script>
